<br>
“So, how long ---”<br>
<br>
“Remember when I had to do research for that family tree project at school?”<br>
<br>
“Vaguely,” Gabe answered.  “But that was ---”<br>
<br>
“A long time ago,” she said, cutting him off once again.  “I know.  I’m sorry.”<br>
<br>
“And – your mom?”<br>
<br>
“Haven’t talked to her,” Chloe said truthfully.  “But Trevor, Kim, and Jake answered a bunch of my questions, and we kind of became…friends – sort of.”<br>
<br>
“Oh.”<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” she said again.  “Listen, Dad, I know that you probably don’t want me talking to them, and I totally understand, but ---” Gabe shook his head and held up a hand.<br>
<br>
“It’s fine.  Really.”<br>
<br>
“What?”<br>
<br>
